#: Game.Levels.QuantifierWorld.L03_UniversalElimination
msgid "Let В§0 be a predicate over a type В§1.\n"
"\n"
"Suppose we have a proof В§2 that for all В§3, В§4 is true.\n"
"\n"
"Then if we are given any particular В§5. We can use В§6 to provide a proof of В§7.\n"
"\n"
"How?\n"
"\n"
"Recall that we can think of proofs of universally quantified statements as *dependent functions*.\n"
"\n"
"Thus, В§8 can be thought of as a function that takes В§9 to a proof В§10 of the proposition В§11.\n"
"\n"
"We say that В§12 is a *dependent* function because the element В§13 proves the proposition В§14, while the element В§15 proves a different proposition, namely В§16.\n"
"\n"
"In particular, В§17 is our desired proof of the proposition В§18."
