#: Game.Levels.CoproductWorld
msgid "Given any types В§0 and В§1 we have studied\n"
"\n"
"* function types В§2 whose elements В§3 are *functions* from В§4 to В§5 and\n"
"\n"
"* product types В§6 whose elements В§7 are *pairs* of elements В§8 and В§9.\n"
"\n"
"In this world, we'll study another binary type forming operation. Given two types В§10 and В§11, there is a type В§12 called the *coproduct type* which has two varieties of elements:\n"
"\n"
"* elements В§13 define elements В§14\n"
"* elements В§15 define elements В§16.\n"
"\n"
"Together, these constructions define the two *introduction rules* for coproduct types. Coproduct types also have an *elimination rule*, which gives a strategy for defining a function В§17 whose inputs belong to a coproduct type and whose outputs take values in an arbitrary type В§18.\n"
"\n"
"This elimination rule tells us that functions out of a coproduct can be defined &ldquo;by cases&rdquo; &mdash; that is, by independently specifying the images of those elements that come from В§19 and those elements that come from В§20.\n"
"\n"
"Collectively, these rules characterize coproduct types and can be used to establish their properties, which we will explore in the levels that follow."
msgstr ""

