#: Game.Levels.ClassicalWorld.L01_ByContradiction
msgid "Let В§0 be a proposition.\n"
"\n"
"We have learned that there is a default strategy to prove В§1, i.e., that В§2 implies В§3.\n"
"\n"
"The strategy is to start by assuming we have a proof В§4, in other words, assuming that В§5 is true.\n"
"\n"
"Then the goal is to derive an element of В§6, also known as a *contradiction*.\n"
"\n"
"This proof strategy is fully compatible with constructive mathematics.\n"
"\n"
"There is a related, by distinct, strategy in classical logic that can be used to prove a proposition В§7 assuming called &ldquo;proof by contradiction&rdquo;. Here one assumes we have a proof В§8, in other words, assuming that В§9 is false.\n"
"\n"
"The goal is again to derive an element of В§10, also known as a contradiction.\n"
"\n"
"Such a proof &mdash; assuming В§11 and then deriving an element of В§12 &mdash; constructs an element of В§13.\n"
"\n"
"In classical logic, there is an implication В§14, which is why &ldquo;proof by contradiction&rdquo; can be used to ultimately prove that В§15 is true.\n"
"\n"
"To prove В§16 in Lean, type В§17 to tell Lean that we are appealing to the proof by contradiction strategy."
msgstr ""

