#: Game.Levels.TypeWorld.L03_ExactElements
msgid "A more elaborate context may contain multiple types and multiple elements, or a mix of types, elements, propositions, and proofs.\n"
"\n"
"Thus, we may require a more precise way to tell Lean which data or hypothesis from our context should be used.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, our context includes two types В§0 and В§1 with three elements between them. Note the use of a space rather than a list to indicate that В§2 and В§3 each define elements of type В§4.\n"
"\n"
"Our goal is to define an element of type В§5 and the tactic В§6 will solve this goal. But this tactic does not convey to the reader which assumption was used.\n"
"\n"
"In this sort of setting, it is better practice to use the tactic В§7. If the goal has type В§8 and there is an element В§9 in the context, then В§10 uses the element В§11 to close the goal.\n"
"\n"
"The В§12 tactic can also be used when the goal is a proposition В§13 and the context includes a proof В§14. Then В§15 will solve the goal.\n"
"\n"
"The tactic В§16 can now be found in the library."
msgstr ""

