#: Game.Levels.TypeWorld.L01_Elements
msgid "An interative theorem prover &mdash; in this case Lean &mdash; helps the user &mdash; this means you &mdash; keep track of the state of a proof or a mathematical construction.\n"
"\n"
"In the В§0 window, Lean keeps track of the В§1 and В§2 &mdash; which together define the hypotheses of a mathematical statement &mdash; as well as the В§3 &mdash; meaning the thing we are trying to prove.\n"
"\n"
"The objects and assumptions together define the mathematical *context* for a given theorem or construction.\n"
"\n"
"Here our context is given by a single type В§4 with a hypothesized element В§5.\n"
"\n"
"On the right-hand side we see the name of a type, which is the *goal* for this level. Here that type is В§6, which means that our goal is to define an element of type В§7.\n"
"\n"
"We have such an element by assumption, and you can type В§8 to tell Lean this. Then type В§9 or click the button В§10 to ask Lean to check your work.\n"
"\n"
"Here В§11 is an example of a *tactic*, which is built into Lean. You can find this in the tactic library on the upper right."
msgstr ""

