#: Game.Levels.NaturalNumbersWorld.L03_Induction
msgid "The *principal of mathematical induction* &mdash; also known as the elimination rule for the type of natural numbers &mdash; is a strategy for proving statements of the form\n"
"\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"where В§1 is a predicate on the natural numbers &mdash; also known as a family of propositions.\n"
"\n"
"The formal statement of this principle is given by the axiom:\n"
"\n"
"В§2\n"
"\n"
"In plain language it says\n"
"\n"
"&ldquo;for any predicate В§3 on the natural numbers, if В§4 is true, and if В§5 implies В§6 for all natural numbers В§7, then В§8 is true.&rdquo;\n"
"\n"
"That is, we can prove В§9 after verifying two things:\n"
"\n"
"* the *base case*: proving that В§10 is true\n"
"* the *inductive step*: proving that for any В§11, В§12 implies В§13.\n"
"\n"
"By combining these hypothesis, from the fact that В§14 is true and В§15 is true, we can conclude that В§16 is true. Then from the fact that В§17 is true, we can conclude that В§18 is true. Then from the fact that В§19 is true, we can conclude that В§20 is true. And so on.\n"
"\n"
"In this level, we will use induction to prove that every natural number is even or odd."
msgstr ""

